news.title: Rents in Canada surge as home prices fall
news.para: The average rent on a 1-bedroom apartment in Canada is up 13.7% from the start of the year, data from Rentals.ca shows, with year-on-year rents surging 18.5% in Toronto and 19.2% in Vancouver.

news.title: Sebi to auction 11 properties of Arise Bhoomi Developers on August 26
news.para: Arise Bhoomi Developers had mobilised over Rs 8 crore during 2013-14 from the public in the name of 'purchase of agricultural land' through its various investment schemes, promising them an expected sum at the end of the contract.

news.title: UltraTech Cement's net profit falls 7% to Rs 1,582 crore in Q1 FY23
news.para: Its revenue from operations was up 28.18 per cent to Rs 15,163.98 crore during the quarter under review as against Rs 11,829.84 crore in the corresponding period of the last fiscal.

news.title: Ansal Buildwell to get Rs 47 crore from SWAMIH fund to complete stalled project in Faridabad
news.para: Ansal Buildwell had launched a residential project 'Ansal Crown Heights' a decade ago in Sector 80, Faridabad, Haryana, in an equal joint venture with a local builder.

news.title: Citizen group offers alternative plans for BDD chawls redevelopment in Mumbai
news.para: The citizen group said that the Mhada’s current redevelopment plan will seriously damage the health of occupants, as well as that of their children for generations to come.

news.title: Over 2,400 houses to be built under PMAY in Mandakalli
news.para: Speaking to reporters, he said the foundation stone will be laid in the presence of district minister ST Somashekhar, housing minister V Somanna, MP Pratap Simha and mayor Sunanda Palanethra. The project is taken up at a cost of Rs 165.45 crore.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh yet to start construction of two lakh houses
news.para: This information was given to Lok Sabha on Thursday by minister for housing and urban affairs, Kaushal Kishore, in reply to a question raised by TDP MP, K Ram Mohan Naidu.

news.title: Realtors may face action for betterment tax default in Jaipur
news.para: An official said post-Covid, the state government had issued orders providing relaxation to developers to deposit betterment levy (25% of the reserve price) in four instalments.

news.title: Bihar RERA to reward for information on rule violation
news.para: ​As per the statement issued by RERA, Bihar, people providing authentic information regarding the violation of the Act, would be rewarded by the authority.

news.title: Ozone Urbana Infra Developers says homebuyers' FIR stayed by Karnataka HC
news.para: A group of 128 customers who, based on the direction of the Magistrate Court, had filed an FIR on July 17 against the Directors of Ozone Urbana Infra Developers Pvt Ltd and several housing financing companies.

news.title: SC order punctures Haryana's logic on amending Punjab Land Preservation Act
news.para: The court order also deconstructs the Haryana government's reasons to amend the PLPA in 2019, lifting it from large tracts of land protected by the law, which was enacted to prevent soil erosion and consequent environmental degradation.

news.title: Chargesheets issued to 10 NBCC officials over Green View project in Gurugram
news.para: ​The ministry said, while NBCC has "adequate" quality control mechanisms, in this case, "poor quality work by the contractor and non-observance of laid down quality assurance protocols by the officials concerned" are the main reasons for lapses.

news.title: Air India in talks to lease 400,000 sq ft at Vatika complex in Gurugram
news.para: ​The erstwhile national airline now owned by the Tata Group has already signed a letter of intent (LoI) for about 200,000 sq ft with the option of doubling the space later, they said.

news.title: Haryana RERA asks 17 builders to refund Rs 50 crore to homebuyers
news.para: ​The Haryana Real Estate Regulatory Authority (HRERA) has issued multiple orders pertaining to 17 builders directing them to refund homebuyers' money along with interest at the rate of 9.70 per cent within 90 days.

news.title: Home sales in USA fall again in June as prices hit new record
news.para: Sales sank 5.4 percent compared to May, toppling to a 5.12 million annual rate, far below what economists were projecting, the National Association of Realtors (NAR) reported.
